column3: “Potent for Sativa, can make you tired if not productive. Smell is very zesty cheezy like. But excellent smoke!”

“Beautiful, purple-tinged bud that even after adequate grinding requires a bit more time in the vape chamber than others to get up to temperature.

Emerald Jane's June 2015 batch is quite potent, and I find the high to be fairly murky and opaque. Not unpleasantly so, but I wouldn't want to hit this if I had any plans afterwards.”
“I'm currently growing her at Instagram.com/StonerBusiness watch her grow through harvest curing and smoking”
“Instant head high... terrific. Hi-stim, sensorial nirvana. My new Favorite.”

“Green Crack level sativa. Massively strong sativa head punch to even the most experienced smokers, some of the frostiest, most trichome rich bud I've ever seen. Smokes surprisingly smooth and gives you a long euphoric high that is so strong that you may find it hard to gather your thoughts and speak them to others. It feels like a massage on your brain.”
“Had in the form of Loud Resin by Refine.  It's a very pleasant sativa, with happy energy and relaxing body high.”
“Surprisingly mellow for a sativa. Keeps me very focused as well.”
“Amazing strain! Beautiful taste, amazing high. I love this strain it's my new favorite. Coupes of hits on the bowl hits up in your head. One blunt makes you fully strong high.”
“Similar to Durban Poison, but with a dreamy head buzz that makes it a good ride.”
“easy super smooth high. very happy ,a Lil giddy but yet focused. great for productivity .”
“Nice Strain, Real Smooth Sativa But Packs a punch on the exhale with zingy After tatste.”
“Great Powerful Medicine Relieves Anxiety, Depression, Mental-Physical-Spiritual PAIN, With An Amazing Ability To Get One Transported To The Mother Ship For Mending Overnight.  YAY!”
